text: Adriana Vinas Joy (born March 1, 1994) is a Puerto Rican female volleyball player. She is a member of the Puerto Rico women's national volleyball team. She participated at the 2017 Volleyball World Grand Prix and 2018 Women's World Volleyball Championship. She played for Long Island University's women's volleyball team. == References == Category:1994 births Category:Puerto Rican volleyball players Category:Living people
